data.enText: a person from modern or ancient Greece
the language of modern or ancient Greece

data.chText: （大学的）学生联谊会会员，女生联谊会会员
data.enText: a member of a fraternity or a sorority at a college or university

data.chText: 我全然不懂；我一窍不通
她努力解释系统如何运作，可我怎么也弄不明白。
data.enText: She tried to explain how the system works, but it's all Greek to me.

value.def: Greek means belonging or relating to Greece.

example.ex: In the Greek general election, the New Democracy party has claimed victory.
example.tran: 新民主党在希腊大选中获胜。

value.def: A Greek is a person who comes from Greece.

example.ex: He had looked through the house for the two Greeks.
example.tran: 他搜遍了整个房子想要找到那两个希腊人。

value.def: Greek is the language used in Greece.
Greek or Ancient Greek was the language used in Greece in ancient times.

example.ex: Teachers warn today that Latin, Greek and other classics will be squeezed out of school timetables.
example.tran: 老师们今天发出警告说，拉丁语、古希腊语和其他古典文学将被挤出学校的课程表。

trans: 希腊式十字架(四臂等长)
希腊风味色拉(用番茄、橄榄和羊奶干酪调制而成)
